title: The Lincoln Tower
description: Beautiful church tower, named after Abraham Lincoln - part of Christ Church. The only part of the original church, built in 1873, that remained after the war.

title: Bar Room Bar
description: Used to be a proper pub called The Tankard before it turned into a chain pub.  It now has bouncers.

title: Morrison Convenience Store
description: Convenience store and till counter for the petrol station.
